Component attribution

This binary distribution combines:

1. llama.cpp upstream
   https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
   MIT License — see above

2. am17an/llama.cpp mtp-clean branch
   PR #22673 — Multi-Token Prediction integration
   MIT License (inherits from llama.cpp upstream)

3. TheTom/llama-cpp-turboquant
   https://github.com/TheTom/llama-cpp-turboquant
   Original TurboQuant kernel port for llama.cpp
   MIT License (inherits from llama.cpp upstream)

4. NJannasch/llama.cpp mtp-turboquant branch
   https://github.com/NJannasch/llama.cpp/tree/mtp-turboquant
   Cherry-pick combining MTP and TurboQuant — the direct source of this build
   MIT License (inherits from llama.cpp upstream)

5. TurboQuant algorithm (concept)
   Zandieh et al., ICLR 2026
   "TurboQuant: Walsh-Hadamard-rotated polar codebook quantization for KV cache"
   Algorithm reference — not source code. The kernel implementations are
   community work by TheTom, AmesianX, and others.

6. NVIDIA CUDA Runtime Libraries (cudart, cublas, cublasLt)
   Bundled DLLs (cudart64_12.dll, cublas64_12.dll, cublasLt64_12.dll)
   These are NVIDIA's redistributable runtime libraries from CUDA Toolkit 12.8.
   Redistribution permitted under the CUDA Toolkit EULA's redistribution clauses.
   Full CUDA EULA: https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/eula/

